{"article_id":"rNlnw3FHjXwhrrBx","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Ferguson , Missouri , was one of hundreds of municipalities","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"designated a `` Playful City USA ''","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"The shooting death of Michael Brown , 18 , by police has put it in the national spotlight","depth":3},{"id":4,"text":"Before Saturday 's police shooting of an African-American teenager , Ferguson , Missouri , was known as one of hundreds of municipalities","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"designated by a national nonprofit as a `` Playful City USA , '' a place","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"where children are supposed to have access to more opportunities","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"to play in their communities .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"But the shooting death of Michael Brown , a college-bound 18-year-old , by a police officer has brought national attention to the mostly black community for another reason .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"Witnesses and residents say","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"the young man was unarmed .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"Police say","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"he tried to take an officer 's gun .","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"Authorities ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"citing threats and safety issues ,","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"have refused to identify the officer .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Protests have turned violent .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Tensions remain high","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"after isolated looting incidents and dozens of arrests in the St. Louis suburb of 22,400 .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"To locals and longtime observers , the tension has been brewing since the 1970s ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"when Ferguson underwent a racial transformation .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Once predominantly white , the city became overwhelmingly black","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"as white families moved out during the racial integration of public schools .","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"At the same time , many African-American families started to move to Ferguson from St. Louis and surrounding communities .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"`` This whole situation has been boiling for a while , ''","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"said Antonio French , a St. Louis alderman","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"who lives five miles from Ferguson .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"`` It 's not just the death of Michael Brown","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"but the way","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"it 's been handled by the local government","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"and the response to the community 's outrage","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"that forced this to boil over . ''","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"Mom :","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"How many times was my son shot ?","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"Mom :","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"How many times was my son shot ?","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"02:09","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"Tensions rise in Missouri teen shooting","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Tensions rise in Missouri teen shooting","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"02:31","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"On the streets in Ferguson","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"On the streets in Ferguson","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"04:15","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"On Thursday , Missouri Gov . Jay Nixon acknowledged long-simmering tensions between the community and police .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"`` This feels a little like an old wound","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"that has been hit again , ''","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"`` The key to this is ... ultimately getting to some of these deeper problems .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"These are deep and existing problems not only in Missouri but in America .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"This has clearly touched a nerve ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"and that nerve is not merely from this horrific incident","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"that happened just a few short days ago . ''","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"Advocates for effective policing contend","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"that law enforcement should reflect the diversity of the community","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"it polices .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"When that is out of balance , however ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"an incident such as the Brown shooting can cause tensions to boil over .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"What 's happening in Ferguson today is a perfect example ,","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"said Beryl Satter , a history professor at Rutgers University in New Jersey .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"`` This is what happens","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"when you have massive racial change in a community","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"and the power structure remains in the hands of whites","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"and the police force acts as this sort of mediating force between the white power structure and what is now a black community","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"and has very little empathy or knowledge about that community . ''","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"Two-thirds of Ferguson 's population is black ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"and yet the mayor is white ,","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"and so are five of the six city council members .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"The police chief is also white .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"There are only three African-Americans on the 53-person police force .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"`` This all gets back to segregation , ''","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"Satter said .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"`` The school boards , the police force , the juvenile courts remain the same .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"The population changes","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"before the power structure changes . ... It happened across the country","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"when there was very rapid resegregation of a town , a neighborhood or a city . ''","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"Ferguson Police Chief Thomas Jackson admitted Wednesday","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"that diversity on the force was a `` constant struggle ''","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"but said","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"race relations were a top priority for his department .","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"He also said","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"the officer","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"who shot Brown","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"was assaulted","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"before opening fire on the young man .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"According to a 2013 report","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"released by the Missouri attorney general ,","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"African-Americans are not under-represented in crime statistics .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"They accounted for 93 % of arrests after traffic stops , 92 % of searches and 86 % of traffic stops .","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"The St. Louis area has always been one of the most racially segregated regions in the country ,","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"according to Satter and other experts .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"It was in St. Louis that a federal judge in 1847 returned Dred Scott to slavery in a decision","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"upheld by the U.S. Supreme Court ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"which ruled","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"that African-Americans were not American citizens","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"and could not sue in federal court .","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"Deadly race riots erupted in East St. Louis in the early 1900s .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"The looting and angry protests","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"that followed Brown 's death ,","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"Satter said ,","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"are part of the `` historical lineage of violence and segregation . ''","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"While all the facts","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"surrounding the Brown shooting","depth":13},{"id":111,"text":"have yet to come out ,","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"Satter said ,","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"the disconnect between the community and law enforcement can have lasting effects .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"`` It 's just a terrible spiral of oppression , ''","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"she said .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"`` The reaction of rioting in response to police brutality is classic .","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"It 's so personal .","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"Other kinds of oppression","depth":15},{"id":119,"text":"that black people face ,","depth":15},{"id":120,"text":"say in the school or other places ,","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"it 's not on your body .","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"It 's not as personally invasive .","depth":14},{"id":123,"text":"But police brutality hurts in a sharper , more profound and immediate way .","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"People can relate to what happened to this boy . ''","depth":13},{"id":125,"text":"Jackson told CNN this week","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"that he was working to improve the diversity of the force .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"Racial profiling ,","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"he said ,","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"was `` strictly forbidden . ''","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"`` We actually have mandatory racial profiling training","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"that we have to take","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"to be certified , ''","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"`` Racial profiling is against our policies .","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"It actually benefits nothing . ''","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"David Klinger , a criminal justice professor at the University of Missouri-St. Louis and a former Los Angeles police officer , said","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"that a more diverse police force does n't always translate into better police relations with a community .","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"`` If the cops are not treating the citizens appropriately ,","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"is it a question of the cops not doing their job right","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"because they 're not trained well","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"or they 're knuckleheads","depth":15},{"id":142,"text":"or they hold racial animus ? ''","depth":15},{"id":143,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"`` Who knows ?","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"But","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"if you bore down","depth":14},{"id":147,"text":"and it turns out","depth":15},{"id":148,"text":"that there 's racial animus ,","depth":15},{"id":149,"text":"then you have a real big problem on top of the lack of professionalism ,","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"because that 's a flashpoint in our society .","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"We have a rough history in America","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"regarding race relations .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"And the police , unfortunately , have been on the wrong side of that . ''","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"Dan Isom , retired chief of police in St. Louis and a criminal justice professor at the University of Missouri-St. Louis , said","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"the diversity of the police rank and file and command definitely affects community relations .","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"`` When you look across the nation ,","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"it 's not uncommon for police departments to have a racial makeup","depth":13},{"id":158,"text":"that is not consistent with the community , ''","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"`` You do n't have a political or community push for improvement","depth":11},{"id":161,"text":"until something like the Michael Brown shooting happens . ''","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"According to the Bureau of Justice Statistics ,","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"about a quarter of police officers across the nation were ethnic minorities in 2007 ,","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"compared with a sixth of officers in 1987 .","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"`` There are so many questions","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"to be asked beyond just the shooting , ''","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"Isom said .","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"`` Certainly , the police department 's makeup , the relationship with the community .","depth":11},{"id":169,"text":"Hopefully , this brings a bigger conversation :","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"Why does this happen in the African-American community ?","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"What are the deeper issues","depth":14},{"id":172,"text":"we have to resolve between communities and police ? ''","depth":14},{"id":173,"text":"Other factors about Ferguson need to be considered ,","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"observers said .","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"According to the 2010 census ,","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"community residents are mostly young ;","depth":12},{"id":177,"text":"the average age is 31 .","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"Median household income is $ 37,000 :","depth":11},{"id":179,"text":"about $ 10,000 less than Missouri as a whole .","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"About one-fifth of Ferguson residents live in poverty .","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"African-Americans are much worse off economically than whites , with a 25 % poverty rate","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"that 's more than twice that of whites ,","depth":13},{"id":183,"text":"according to the most recent government estimates from two years ago .","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"Their median income is only about 60 % that of their white counterparts .","depth":11},{"id":185,"text":"`` Ferguson 's black community is a very transient community ,","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"living in rental housing , ''","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"said French , the St. Louis alderman .","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"`` Not many people register","depth":11},{"id":189,"text":"to vote ,","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"and even less participate in elections . ...","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"People are living day to day out there ,","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"and part of their daily existence is negative encounters with the police .","depth":12},{"id":193,"text":"They want to be heard .","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"They want their frustration to be recognized . ''","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":389,"left":0,"right":388,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":388,"left":197,"right":387,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":197,"left":196,"right":3,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":196,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":387,"left":244,"right":386,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":224,"right":243,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":224,"left":201,"right":223,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":200,"right":8,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":200,"left":4,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":5,"right":198,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":198,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":210,"right":222,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":207,"right":209,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":207,"left":204,"right":206,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":204,"left":202,"right":203,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":202,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":203,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":206,"left":205,"right":15,"relation":"same-unit","n